WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.700 --> 00:00:10.100
Anyone can claim their kitchen is safe. Magppie proves it — seven ways, in this exact order every time.

2
00:00:11.900 --> 00:00:20.533
Stain safe: the surface is non-porous, so coffee, turmeric, oil wipe off — they don't sink in.

3
00:00:22.333 --> 00:00:26.333
Scratch safe: daily chopping doesn't leave marks.

4
00:00:28.133 --> 00:00:32.733
High load bearing: every drawer holds up to 60 kilograms.

5
00:00:34.533 --> 00:00:39.733
Fire safe: the stone doesn't catch fire or help flames spread.

6
00:00:41.533 --> 00:00:54.333
Water safe: a 30-day test — a wood panel and a stone sample, both submerged. The wood swelled and weakened. The stone came out exactly as it went in.

7
00:00:56.133 --> 00:01:04.967
Impact safe: a heavy ceramic jar dropped directly onto the surface stayed intact — stronger than granite.

8
00:01:06.767 --> 00:01:14.067
And more storage: up to 62% more than a standard kitchen, sized to fit large Indian plates.

9
00:01:15.867 --> 00:01:20.600
Seven pillars. Proof, not promises.

